# CNN Learn - Interactive CNN Learning Platform

## Project Overview

A professional, TensorFlow Playground-style interactive web platform for learning Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) through visual simulations and hands-on experimentation.

## Current Status

✅ **Completed Features:**
- Full CNN simulation engine (TypeScript-based, no ML libraries)
- Interactive CNN architecture builder using React Flow
- Feature map visualization system
- Kernel editor with real-time preview
- Training simulation dashboard with Recharts
- 6 interactive learning lessons
- Gamification system (XP, badges, challenges)
- User dashboard and progress tracking
- Leaderboard system
- Landing page with modern design
- Supabase database integration
- Routing with React Router

✅ **Working Components:**
- Matrix operations (2D/3D creation, padding, normalization)
- Convolution operations with configurable kernels
- Pooling layers (max/average)
- Activation functions (ReLU, Sigmoid, Tanh, Softmax)
- Dense layers with weight initialization
- Forward pass orchestration
- Sample datasets (lines, circles, digits)

## Tech Stack

- **Framework**: React 18 + TypeScript + Vite
- **State Management**: Zustand (with persist middleware)
- **UI**: TailwindCSS + Custom components
- **Visualization**: React Flow, Recharts, HTML Canvas
- **Animation**: Framer Motion
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL)
- **Routing**: React Router v6

